ReviewTitle: Good case but clear yellows over time
ReviewContent: Very solid case that offers great protection but part of the clear case yellowed after 4 months of use.

ReviewTitle: Pretty Case, but I'd rather have saved some money on a cheaper one
ReviewContent:
To be clear, I do like the design of this case.  It feels more premium than some of the cheaper models online with a good mix of a hard back (to help with wireless charging) and the soft bumper around the edge. This should be expected of a company like OtterBox at this point and at this price point.

I have dropped the phone once or twice from roughly 3 feet up  without a sign of damage to the device, so it does its job well.

However, I have to give it two stars for how poorly it has held up now that I'm almost one year to the day since I ordered it.

As you can see in the photos, the device yellows/browns pretty severely on about half the case (mostly the contact points for buttons and the charge port. Additionally, I noticed that the bottom of the case has started to completely separate.  Finally, as my finger points to in the image of the magsafe outline, the rectangular piece has fully fallen out of the case.  It is at least stuck to the back of my phone, so everything still functions, but worth noting.

I wouldn't care so much about the discoloration if this case weren't 2-3x the cost of some of the usual cases I've bought on here and if this hadn't all happened in under a year! My case on my last iPhone was roughly $10 and lasted 3 years before needing a replacement.  I'll be replacing this with something cheaper.
I was actually kind of surprised how quickly this phone case fell apart considering it’s an otterbox. Was great while it lasted though! I love the ability to remove the pop socket!
The cover discolored and stretched around the volumes buttons and charger port.

ReviewTitle: Works fine but anchor magnet fell out
ReviewContent: I love the clear basic case. It’s a hard plastic back and flexible bumper. Keeps my phone protected from falls and scratches. Only complaints are that the soft plastic always yellows and the little anchor magnet fell out when I took the case off. Honestly looks a little rough for only using it for 6 months but it’s cheaper than the apple case and probably provides better protection.

I really needed something that worked with my magsafe phone holder in my car. This baby works wonders when hitting the potholes of Atlanta and never falls off.  I've owned this for a few months now and can honestly say as a person who can be messy/clumsy/spills things easily - it has NOT yellowed, is VERY durable (I unintentionally) drop it at least once per day), and overall a solid case.

We purchased these August 2022 and they’re already pulling away from our phones. Both of them.
